#1 Stage IIIB (T2, N2a, M0) adenocarcinoma of the rectum, status-post APR
We had a fairly extensive discussion today with Mr. Klassen and his family with regard to our followup recommendations for his recently resected rectal cancer.  The patient is currently doing well postoperatively from his resection.  We discussed that his first goal is to recover from the surgery.  We would then like to see him back in GI Clinic in about four to six-weeks' time.  When we see him in clinic, we will discuss options such as chemotherapy and radiation adjuvant treatments.  The patient has already visited with the Radiation Oncology Team as well here in the hospital.  We will coordinate our plan with them at that time.  We will need to see how the patient's performance status is at that time as well when formulating his adjuvant plan.  I answered several of the patient's and his family's questions; however, we will address things in more detail at that postoperative followup appointment in four to six-weeks.
Thank-you for allowing us to consult on Mr. Klassen's care.  Please do not hesitate to call us with any questions.  Our pager is 269-675-15216.

[end section id="20112"]

